02/06/2006
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Foreign Minister Ilinka Mitreva was in Athens on Thursday (1 June) for talks with Greek Deputy Foreign Minister Evripidis Stylianidis, focusing primarily on economic co-operation issues. 
According to a statement from Mitreva's office, they discussed speeding up implementation of the pan-European Transport Corridor 10, as well as projects included in the Greek Plan for Economic Reconstruction of the Balkans that involve Macedonia. 
After the meeting, it was announced that the countries plan to launch a joint project to build a water purifying station in the Macedonian border region of Gevgelija. 
(Makfax, ANA - 01/06/06)
